## Decision Framework

After reading `results.csv` and `args.yaml` from the latest run, classify the situation and act.

### Where the inputs come from

Your per-round prompt has three sections (see yolo_folder_skill.md "How the
per-round prompt is built"):

- **`## Verified facts`** — machine-extracted: best so far, run trajectory,
  consecutive failures. Use these numbers; do not re-derive by reading CSVs
  unless you need an epoch finer than what's surfaced.
- **`## Run history`** — newest 3 runs full detail, older collapsed.
- **`## Claude's notes`** — your previous-self's prose. Treat as hypothesis.

When the trajectory in Verified facts shows recent improvement, keep
exploring with Actions A-J. When it plateaus across multiple rounds, the
right move is usually **more / better data** (collect more labeled
examples, audit existing labels) rather than more training compute —
small AOI datasets saturate quickly and additional epochs mostly fit noise.

