## Lessons Learned (from prior sessions)

1. **`optimizer=auto` overrides lr0 to 0.002** — ALWAYS use `"OPTIMIZER": "AdamW"` explicitly to control LR
2. **Fine-tuning from best.pt often fails on nano models** — the warmup phase disrupts learned features; prefer training from pretrained weights
3. **Resolution (IMGSZ) is the #1 lever** for high-res source images — try IMGSZ=1024 early
4. **Short training (100 epochs) can beat long training (2000 epochs)** for nano models — don't assume longer is better
5. **Small validation sets (<200 images) cause high metric variance** — single-epoch metrics may be partly luck
6. **LR schedule depends on epoch count** — LR_FINAL=0.002 with 2000 epochs decays too slowly; link LR_FINAL recommendation to EPOCHS setting

